org.araneaframework.core.util
Class SessionTreeRenderingMessage

java.lang.Object
  org.araneaframework.core.util.SessionTreeRenderingMessage
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Message
public class SessionTreeRenderingMessage
extends Object
implements Message

A special message that can be used to render the components tree. It does not go to all components because not all of higher level components are accessible. However, most of the components are still available in the result.

The recommended usage of this class is through the execute(Environment) or execute(Environment, ItemDecorator) methods.

Since:
1.2.3
Author:
Martti Tamm (martti@araneaframework.org)

Constructor Detail

SessionTreeRenderingMessage

public SessionTreeRenderingMessage(SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ItemDecorator decorator)
The constructor for creating an instance of the message. Although the static execute(...) method are more preferred, you can still use the message separately. Also note that the contructor requires ItemDecorator, which may be null to use the default implementation for decorating the output.

Parameters:
decorator - The decorator that is used for generating the string output. You may provide a custom implementation, or null to use the default.

getComponents

public List<SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ComponentItem> getComponents()
Returns the components found by this message. The items in this list are of type SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ComponentItem. Note that the returned list may contain only one component item because actually the component will return its child components through SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ComponentItem.getChildren().

Returns:
A list of SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ComponentItems.

compose

protected void compose(SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ItemDecorator decorator,
                       StringBuffer sb,
                       SessionTreeRenderingMessage.ComponentItem item,
                       int level)
An internal solution for composing the StringBuffer result recursively.

Parameters:
decorator - The decorator used for composing the StringBuffer.
sb - The StringBuffer where the output is stored.
item - The component that is added to the output. Its children are also recursively processed by this method.
level - The depth of the item compared to the root component in the results.
